2.1.1 Memory Allocation
-----------------------

Portable `STREAMS' modules and drivers will always allocate memory using the
SVR4 memory allocators/deallocators: *note (*manpages*)kmem_alloc(9)::, *note
(*manpages*)kmem_zalloc(9):: and *note (*manpages*)kmem_free(9)::.

Additional eligible allocators are:

*note (*manpages*)rmallocmap(9):: *note (*manpages*)rmfreemap(9):: *note
(*manpages*)rmalloc(9):: *note (*manpages*)rmalloc_wait(9):: *note
(*manpages*)rmfree(9):: *note (*manpages*)rminit(9):: *note
(*manpages*)rmsetwant(9):: *note (*manpages*)rmwanted(9)::

Unfortunately, these resource map allocators are not available on `AIX' so, if
portability to the `AIX PSE' is important, then do not use these allocators.

Additional eligible allocators are:

*note (*manpages*)kmem_fast_alloc(9):: *note (*manpages*)kmem_fast_free(9)::


